<div class="evc-content">
          <h2>The Economic Times</h2>
          <p style="text-align:justify;">As artificial intelligence reshapes industries, hospitality faces a distinct challenge: preserving human connection while embracing automation. At the India AI Impact Summit, Dr. D. Premachandra Sagar, Founder and Pro-Chancellor, Dayananda Sagar Univerity, discusses how AI can transform training, service standards, and operational efficiency — without diluting the emotional core of hospitality. 
</p>
